  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "As discovered in #4651, there's a regression in v2.11.0-rc.3 that's not present in v2.10.0.\r\n\r\nIn v2.10.0, environment variables and flags are respected:\r\n\r\n```\r\n><> helm ls --tls --tls-cert=/foo\r\ncould not read x509 key pair (cert: \"/foo\", key: \"/home/bacongobbler/.helm/key.pem\"): can't load key pair from cert /foo and key /home/bacongobbler/.helm/key.pem: open /foo: no such file or directory\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn v2.11.0-rc.3 though, these flags are not being respected:\r\n\r\n```\r\n><> ./linux-amd64/helm version -c\r\nClient: &version.Version{SemVer:\"v2.11.0-rc.3\", GitCommit:\"28d295be2a94115b786ee277dffcc2b5483bde47\", GitTreeState:\"clean\"}\r\n><> ./linux-amd64/helm ls --tls-cert=/foo --tls\r\ncould not read x509 key pair (cert: \"/home/bacongobbler/.helm/cert.pem\", key: \"/home/bacongobbler/.helm/key.pem\"): can't load key pair from cert /home/bacongobbler/.helm/cert.pem and key /home/bacongobbler/.helm/key.pem: open /home/bacongobbler/.helm/cert.pem: no such file or directory\r\n```\r\n",
